text: Kitzbühel is a small medieval town in Tyrol, Austria. It is the administrative center of the Kitzbühel district (Bezirk). As of 2018, 8,272 people live there. It is in the Kitzbühel Alps along the river Kitzbüheler Ache and about 100 km (62 mi) east of the state capital Innsbruck. Kitzbühel is a ski resort of international renown and its ski season lasts from mid October to early May.
